id and liqui d domestic and industrial waste, including its deposition on land, disposal of sewage sludge and incineration of municipal waste;  – control the production, sale, use and disposal of certain toxic, environmentally-persistent substances, e.g. organohalogen c ompounds (PCBs, brominated flame retardants, etc.), lead , cadmium and mercury compounds;
